Vice President Mike Pence welcomed Taoiseach (Prime Minister) of Ireland, Leo Varadkar, to the Vice President's Residence in Washington, D.C. as part of the St. Patrick's Day celebrations. Pence expressed gratitude for the strong relationship between the United States and Ireland and highlighted the contributions of Irish Americans to the country. He also mentioned the economic ties between the two countries and expressed the administration's commitment to strengthening those ties. Pence mentioned that the United States stands with Ireland as the United Kingdom deals with Brexit and looks forward to discussing expanded trade and a new trade agreement with Ireland. Pence also announced that he will be making an official visit to Ireland with his mother. He concluded by expressing his deep love and appreciation for his Irish heritage.